Definition.WordDefinition:
artwork \artwork\ n. (Publishing) photographs, illustrations, or other visual representations other than the text, in a printed publication.
Syn: art, graphics, nontextual matter. [WordNet 1.5]
artwork n : photographs or other visual representations in a printed publication; "the publisher was responsible for all the artwork in the book" [syn: {art}, {graphics}, {nontextual matter}]
